37/*
38 * CFF2 -- Compact Font Format (CFF) Version 2
39 * https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/cff2
40 */
41#define HB_OT_TAG_cff2 HB_TAG('C','F','F','2')
42
43typedef CFFIndex<HBUINT32> CFF2Index;
44template <typename Type> struct CFF2IndexOf : CFFIndexOf<HBUINT32, Type> {};

49typedef FDSelect3_4<HBUINT32, HBUINT16> FDSelect4;
50typedef FDSelect3_4_Range<HBUINT32, HBUINT16> FDSelect4_Range;

52struct CFF2FDSelect
53{
54 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c, const CFF2FDSelect &src, unsigned int num_glyphs)
55 {
56 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
57 unsigned int size = src.get_size (num_glyphs);
58 CFF2FDSelect *dest = c->allocate_size<CFF2FDSelect> (size);
59 if (unlikely (!dest)) return_trace (false);
60 hb_memcpy (dst: dest, src: &src, len: size);
61 return_trace (true);
62 }
63
64 unsigned int get_size (unsigned int num_glyphs) const
65 {
66 switch (format)
67 {
68 case 0: return format.static_size + u.format0.get_size (num_glyphs);
69 case 3: return format.static_size + u.format3.get_size ();
70 case 4: return format.static_size + u.format4.get_size ();
71 default:return 0;
72 }
73 }
74
75 hb_codepoint_t get_fd (hb_codepoint_t glyph) const
76 {
77 if (this == &Null (CFF2FDSelect))
78 return 0;
79
80 switch (format)
81 {
82 case 0: return u.format0.get_fd (glyph);
83 case 3: return u.format3.get_fd (glyph);
84 case 4: return u.format4.get_fd (glyph);
85 default:return 0;
86 }
87 }
88
89 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c, unsigned int fdcount) const
90 {
91 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
92 if (unlikely (!c->check_struct (this)))
93 return_trace (false);
94
95 switch (format)
96 {
97 case 0: return_trace (u.format0.sanitize (c, fdcount));
98 case 3: return_trace (u.format3.sanitize (c, fdcount));
99 case 4: return_trace (u.format4.sanitize (c, fdcount));
100 default:return_trace (false);
101 }
102 }
103
104 HBUINT8 format;
105 union {
106 FDSelect0 format0;
107 FDSelect3 format3;
108 FDSelect4 format4;
109 } u;
110 public:
111 DEFINE_SIZE_MIN (2);
112};
113
114struct CFF2VariationStore
115{
116 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
117 {
118 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
119 return_trace (likely (c->check_struct (this)) && c->check_range (&varStore, size) && varStore.sanitize (c));
120 }
121
122 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c, const CFF2VariationStore *varStore)
123 {
124 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
125 unsigned int size_ = varStore->get_size ();
126 CFF2VariationStore *dest = c->allocate_size<CFF2VariationStore> (size: size_);
127 if (unlikely (!dest)) return_trace (false);
128 hb_memcpy (dst: dest, src: varStore, len: size_);
129 return_trace (true);
130 }
131
132 unsigned int get_size () const { return HBUINT16::static_size + size; }
133
134 HBUINT16 size;
135 VariationStore varStore;
136
137 DEFINE_SIZE_MIN (2 + VariationStore::min_size);
138};

154struct cff2_top_dict_opset_t : top_dict_opset_t<>
155{
156 static void process_op (op_code_t op, num_interp_env_t& env, cff2_top_dict_values_t& dictval)
157 {
158 switch (op) {
159 case OpCode_FontMatrix:
160 {
161 dict_val_t val;
162 val.init ();
163 dictval.add_op (op, str_ref: env.str_ref);
164 env.clear_args ();
165 }
166 break;
167
168 case OpCode_vstore:
169 dictval.vstoreOffset = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
170 env.clear_args ();
171 break;
172 case OpCode_FDSelect:
173 dictval.FDSelectOffset = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
174 env.clear_args ();
175 break;
176
177 default:
178 SUPER::process_op (op, env, dictval);
179 /* Record this operand below if stack is empty, otherwise done */
180 if (!env.argStack.is_empty ()) return;
181 }
182
183 if (unlikely (env.in_error ())) return;
184
185 dictval.add_op (op, str_ref: env.str_ref);
186 }
187
188 typedef top_dict_opset_t<> SUPER;
189};

203struct cff2_font_dict_opset_t : dict_opset_t
204{
205 static void process_op (op_code_t op, num_interp_env_t& env, cff2_font_dict_values_t& dictval)
206 {
207 switch (op) {
208 case OpCode_Private:
209 dictval.privateDictInfo.offset = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
210 dictval.privateDictInfo.size = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
211 env.clear_args ();
212 break;
213
214 default:
215 SUPER::process_op (op, env);
216 if (!env.argStack.is_empty ())
217 return;
218 }
219
220 if (unlikely (env.in_error ())) return;
221
222 dictval.add_op (op, str_ref: env.str_ref);
223 }
224
225 private:
226 typedef dict_opset_t SUPER;
227};

249struct cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t : num_interp_env_t
250{
251 cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t (const hb_ubytes_t &str) :
252 num_interp_env_t (str) {}
253
254 void process_vsindex ()
255 {
256 if (likely (!seen_vsindex))
257 {
258 set_ivs (argStack.pop_uint ());
259 }
260 seen_vsindex = true;
261 }
262
263 unsigned int get_ivs () const { return ivs; }
264 void set_ivs (unsigned int ivs_) { ivs = ivs_; }
265
266 protected:
267 unsigned int ivs = 0;
268 bool seen_vsindex = false;
269};

271struct cff2_private_dict_opset_t : dict_opset_t
272{
273 static void process_op (op_code_t op, cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t& env, cff2_private_dict_values_t& dictval)
274 {
275 num_dict_val_t val;
276 val.init ();
277
278 switch (op) {
279 case OpCode_StdHW:
280 case OpCode_StdVW:
281 case OpCode_BlueScale:
282 case OpCode_BlueShift:
283 case OpCode_BlueFuzz:
284 case OpCode_ExpansionFactor:
285 case OpCode_LanguageGroup:
286 case OpCode_BlueValues:
287 case OpCode_OtherBlues:
288 case OpCode_FamilyBlues:
289 case OpCode_FamilyOtherBlues:
290 case OpCode_StemSnapH:
291 case OpCode_StemSnapV:
292 env.clear_args ();
293 break;
294 case OpCode_Subrs:
295 dictval.subrsOffset = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
296 env.clear_args ();
297 break;
298 case OpCode_vsindexdict:
299 env.process_vsindex ();
300 dictval.ivs = env.get_ivs ();
301 env.clear_args ();
302 break;
303 case OpCode_blenddict:
304 break;
305
306 default:
307 dict_opset_t::process_op (op, env);
308 if (!env.argStack.is_empty ()) return;
309 break;
310 }
311
312 if (unlikely (env.in_error ())) return;
313
314 dictval.add_op (op, str_ref: env.str_ref, v: val);
315 }
316};

318struct cff2_private_dict_opset_subset_t : dict_opset_t
319{
320 static void process_op (op_code_t op, cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t& env, cff2_private_dict_values_subset_t& dictval)
321 {
322 switch (op) {
323 case OpCode_BlueValues:
324 case OpCode_OtherBlues:
325 case OpCode_FamilyBlues:
326 case OpCode_FamilyOtherBlues:
327 case OpCode_StdHW:
328 case OpCode_StdVW:
329 case OpCode_BlueScale:
330 case OpCode_BlueShift:
331 case OpCode_BlueFuzz:
332 case OpCode_StemSnapH:
333 case OpCode_StemSnapV:
334 case OpCode_LanguageGroup:
335 case OpCode_ExpansionFactor:
336 env.clear_args ();
337 break;
338
339 case OpCode_blenddict:
340 env.clear_args ();
341 return;
342
343 case OpCode_Subrs:
344 dictval.subrsOffset = env.argStack.pop_uint ();
345 env.clear_args ();
346 break;
347
348 default:
349 SUPER::process_op (op, env);
350 if (!env.argStack.is_empty ()) return;
351 break;
352 }
353
354 if (unlikely (env.in_error ())) return;
355
356 dictval.add_op (op, str_ref: env.str_ref);
357 }
358
359 private:
360 typedef dict_opset_t SUPER;
361};

366struct CFF2FDArray : FDArray<HBUINT32>
367{
368 /* FDArray::serialize does not compile without this partial specialization */

370 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c, ITER it, OP_SERIALIZER& opszr)
371 { return FDArray<HBUINT32>::serialize<cff2_font_dict_values_t, table_info_t> (c, it, opszr); }
372};

380struct cff2
381{
382 static constexpr hb_tag_t tableTag = HB_OT_TAG_cff2;
383
384 bool sanitize (hb_sanitize_context_t *c) const
385 {
386 TRACE_SANITIZE (this);
387 return_trace (c->check_struct (this) &&
388 likely (version.major == 2));
389 }
390
391 template <typename PRIVOPSET, typename PRIVDICTVAL>
392 struct accelerator_templ_t
393 {
394 accelerator_templ_t (hb_face_t *face)
395 {
396 topDict.init ();
397 fontDicts.init ();
398 privateDicts.init ();
399
400 this->blob = sc.reference_table<cff2> (face);
401
402 /* setup for run-time santization */
403 sc.init (b: this->blob);
404 sc.start_processing ();
405
406 const OT::cff2 *cff2 = this->blob->template as<OT::cff2> ();
407
408 if (cff2 == &Null (OT::cff2))
409 goto fail;
410
411 { /* parse top dict */
412 hb_ubytes_t topDictStr = (cff2 + cff2->topDict).as_ubytes (l: cff2->topDictSize);
413 if (unlikely (!topDictStr.sanitize (&sc))) goto fail;
414 num_interp_env_t env (topDictStr);
415 cff2_top_dict_interpreter_t top_interp (env);
416 topDict.init ();
417 if (unlikely (!top_interp.interpret (topDict))) goto fail;
418 }
419
420 globalSubrs = &StructAtOffset<CFF2Subrs> (P: cff2, offset: cff2->topDict + cff2->topDictSize);
421 varStore = &StructAtOffsetOrNull<CFF2VariationStore> (P: cff2, offset: topDict.vstoreOffset);
422 charStrings = &StructAtOffsetOrNull<CFF2CharStrings> (P: cff2, offset: topDict.charStringsOffset);
423 fdArray = &StructAtOffsetOrNull<CFF2FDArray> (P: cff2, offset: topDict.FDArrayOffset);
424 fdSelect = &StructAtOffsetOrNull<CFF2FDSelect> (P: cff2, offset: topDict.FDSelectOffset);
425
426 if (((varStore != &Null (CFF2VariationStore)) && unlikely (!varStore->sanitize (&sc))) ||
427 (charStrings == &Null (CFF2CharStrings)) || unlikely (!charStrings->sanitize (&sc)) ||
428 (globalSubrs == &Null (CFF2Subrs)) || unlikely (!globalSubrs->sanitize (&sc)) ||
429 (fdArray == &Null (CFF2FDArray)) || unlikely (!fdArray->sanitize (&sc)) ||
430 (((fdSelect != &Null (CFF2FDSelect)) && unlikely (!fdSelect->sanitize (&sc, fdArray->count)))))
431 goto fail;
432
433 num_glyphs = charStrings->count;
434 if (num_glyphs != sc.get_num_glyphs ())
435 goto fail;
436
437 fdCount = fdArray->count;
438 if (!privateDicts.resize (fdCount))
439 goto fail;
440
441 /* parse font dicts and gather private dicts */
442 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < fdCount; i++)
443 {
444 const hb_ubytes_t fontDictStr = (*fdArray)[i];
445 if (unlikely (!fontDictStr.sanitize (&sc))) goto fail;
446 cff2_font_dict_values_t *font;
447 num_interp_env_t env (fontDictStr);
448 cff2_font_dict_interpreter_t font_interp (env);
449 font = fontDicts.push ();
450 if (unlikely (font == &Crap (cff2_font_dict_values_t))) goto fail;
451 font->init ();
452 if (unlikely (!font_interp.interpret (*font))) goto fail;
453
454 const hb_ubytes_t privDictStr = StructAtOffsetOrNull<UnsizedByteStr> (P: cff2, offset: font->privateDictInfo.offset).as_ubytes (l: font->privateDictInfo.size);
455 if (unlikely (!privDictStr.sanitize (&sc))) goto fail;
456 cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t env2 (privDictStr);
457 dict_interpreter_t<PRIVOPSET, PRIVDICTVAL, cff2_priv_dict_interp_env_t> priv_interp (env2);
458 privateDicts[i].init ();
459 if (unlikely (!priv_interp.interpret (privateDicts[i]))) goto fail;
460
461 privateDicts[i].localSubrs = &StructAtOffsetOrNull<CFF2Subrs> (&privDictStr[0], privateDicts[i].subrsOffset);
462 if (privateDicts[i].localSubrs != &Null (CFF2Subrs) &&
463 unlikely (!privateDicts[i].localSubrs->sanitize (&sc)))
464 goto fail;
465 }
466
467
468 return;
469
470 fail:
471 _fini ();
472 }
473 ~accelerator_templ_t () { _fini (); }
474 void _fini ()
475 {
476 sc.end_processing ();
477 topDict.fini ();
478 fontDicts.fini ();
479 privateDicts.fini ();
480 hb_blob_destroy (blob);
481 blob = nullptr;
482 }
483
484 hb_map_t *create_glyph_to_sid_map () const
485 {
486 return nullptr;
487 }
488
489 bool is_valid () const { return blob; }
490
491 protected:
492 hb_sanitize_context_t sc;
493
494 public:
495 hb_blob_t *blob = nullptr;
496 cff2_top_dict_values_t topDict;
497 const CFF2Subrs *globalSubrs = nullptr;
498 const CFF2VariationStore *varStore = nullptr;
499 const CFF2CharStrings *charStrings = nullptr;
500 const CFF2FDArray *fdArray = nullptr;
501 const CFF2FDSelect *fdSelect = nullptr;
502 unsigned int fdCount = 0;
503
504 hb_vector_t<cff2_font_dict_values_t> fontDicts;
505 hb_vector_t<PRIVDICTVAL> privateDicts;
506
507 unsigned int num_glyphs = 0;
508 };

510 struct accelerator_t : accelerator_templ_t<cff2_private_dict_opset_t, cff2_private_dict_values_t>
511 {
512 accelerator_t (hb_face_t *face) : accelerator_templ_t (face) {}
513
514 HB_INTERNAL bool get_extents (hb_font_t *font,
515 hb_codepoint_t glyph,
516 hb_glyph_extents_t *extents) const;
517 HB_INTERNAL bool paint_glyph (hb_font_t *font, hb_codepoint_t glyph, hb_paint_funcs_t *funcs, void *data, hb_color_t foreground) const;
518 HB_INTERNAL bool get_path (hb_font_t *font, hb_codepoint_t glyph, hb_draw_session_t &draw_session) const;
519 };
520
521 typedef accelerator_templ_t<cff2_private_dict_opset_subset_t, cff2_private_dict_values_subset_t> accelerator_subset_t;
522
523 bool subset (hb_subset_context_t *c) const { return hb_subset_cff2 (c); }
524
525 public:
526 FixedVersion<HBUINT8> version; /* Version of CFF2 table. set to 0x0200u */
527 NNOffsetTo<TopDict, HBUINT8> topDict; /* headerSize = Offset to Top DICT. */
528 HBUINT16 topDictSize; /* Top DICT size */
529
530 public:
531 DEFINE_SIZE_STATIC (5);
532};
